text: Maysa Zaid Mahmoud Jbarah (born 20 September 1989) is a Kuwaiti-born Jordanian footballer who plays as a forward for the Jordan women's national team. Jbarah scored the first goal for the Jordan national football team at the 2010 Asian Games in the 1-10 defeat to hosts China. She also scored the first goal for her country in the AFC Women's Asian Cup in the 2013 edition in the 1-3 defeat to hosts Vietnam. ==References== == External links == * Category:1989 births Category:Asian Games competitors for Jordan Category:Footballers at the 2010 Asian Games Category:Footballers at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Jordan women's international footballers Category:Jordanian women's footballers Category:Jordanian women's futsal players Category:Kuwaiti footballers Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Kuwait City Category:Women's association football forwards
